title: Big Thread about OIDC: SSO, SLI, etc.
author: lafenicenera
text:
So almost a week ago I asked this rather big question about OIDC concepts on Stack overflow. I already knew that it was almost impossible to get an answer for such question there, but due to the lack of an actual community regarding OIDC, OAuth2, SSO and all such themes, I tried anyway.
I don't want this to just be a simple redirect to my stack overflow question. Instead I'd like this to be a thread where people can join sharing their opinions and experience about what I asked in order to have and share a collective knowledge base.
Even though OIDC is standardized, there are so mani scenarios in real life applications that should be addressed and documented.
